description.narrative: The year 2020 was marked by a new dynamic in the Tunisian political landscape, with a;new president and new parliament but it was also characterized by;political instability (3 new government in less than a year) coupled with the sanitary and socio-economic impact of the COVID-19 pandemic. This led UNICEF to strengthen its advocacy to ensure;children and their rights are not dropped and remain high in the political agenda and priorities addressing the crisis, particularly for the most vulnerable children. | Status:Met | As-of Date:05/01/2021
